	dprr:hasNoteText "See PIR² 1.260, on his son." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8324> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8324" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These men were witnesses to the resolutions of the Senate reported by Caelius to Cicero in Fam. 8.8.5-6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7686> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7686" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Perhaps identifiable with the CAP who issued coins as an officer of the triumviri at Lipara in 37-36 (MRR 2.405-406; Grant, FITA 52-54). (TJC) See MRR 2.462; Wiseman NM 215-216, no. 53.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6872> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6872" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 51 (Cic. Fam. 8.8.5). See 51, note." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6554> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6554" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tac. Ann. 3.75, a praetorius; cf. Fast. Cap., Degrassi 60f., 141, 528f., his son held the consulship in 5 A. D." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5438> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5438" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "It is apparent that these senators are arranged in the order of seniority. L. Villius Annalis therefore held the praetorship before 57, and L. Ateius Capito and M. Eppius were ex- Quaestors in 51." .
